{
  "stem": "6052.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "This was when the hate wave increased and the Jews were-- stronger-- stronger measures were taken against the Jews, and arrests were made.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And so we were told we are going to be safer at the Polish consulate.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was told by-- by other Jews who said go there, go there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all went there, and when I read-- at that time, about 1,300 Jews went to the Polish consulate just to sit there and feel safe because we were told this territory where we are going to be of the Polish consulate is safe, which was never so because this was just an assumption.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after three days, they relaxed their threats to arrest Jews, and we came home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But vividly in my-- in my mind is when the Jews were taken out of their apartments and put into the [INAUDIBLE], which was a very small stream with a bridge over it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the small stream, Jews were herded into, and they're spat upon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Those who had beards, the beards were cut off, and so they were humiliated to a terrible, terrible degree.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was all the beginning, and this was all before the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Kristallnacht simplifies-- they [? are ?] simply shows the day where an organized attack was committed against Jews all over Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And stores were looted, and synagogues were burnt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I went through the streets, and I saw myself the Sefer Torah, the holy books-- all was thrown out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And Leipzig, all the Jewish-- most of the Jewish holy institutions were in fire.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there, they wrote about it, and there are pictures about it, and this became then history.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They saw the stones which were taken, which will remained after the-- after the fire, and that they sold it to builders.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
